info.title: Azure Location Based Services
info.description: Azure Location Based Services REST APIs

api-version.name: api-version
api-version.description: Version number of Azure LBS API.  Current version is 1.0

zoom.name: zoom
zoom.description: Zoom level for desired tile.  0 to 18 for raster tiles, 0 through 20 for vector tiles

x.name: x
x.description: X index for the desired tile, based on Spherical Mercator projection coordinate system (EPSG:3857)

y.name: y
y.description: Y index for the desired tile, based on Spherical Mercator projection coordinate system (EPSG:3857)

query.name: query
query.description: The applicable query string and/or coordinates

400.description: Bad request: one or more parameters were incorrectly specified or are mutually exclusive.

401.description: Unauthorized: Access is denied due to invalid credentials.

404.description: Not Found: the requested resource could not be found, but it may be available again in the future.

500.description: An error occurred while processing the request. Please try again later.

get.description: Get the traffic incident detail for a given coordinates

body.message: Bad request: one or more parameters were incorrectly specified or are mutually exclusive.
Unauthorized: Access is denied due to invalid credentials.
Not Found: the requested resource could not be found, but it may be available again in the future.
An error occurred while processing the request. Please try again later.

parameters.name: style
parameters.description: The style that will be used to render the traffic tile in the Maps API. This will have an effect on the coordinates of traffic incidents in the reply.  Valid values are s1, s2, s3 and night

parameters.name: boundingbox
parameters.description: The corners of the area to report on, expressed in the projection specified. These are two latitude-longitude pairs describing corners of the bounding box. First pair for lower left corner and second for upper right. All values should be separated by commas

parameters.name: trafficmodelid
parameters.description: Number referencing traffic model. This can be obtained from the Viewport API. It is updated every minute, and is valid for two minutes before it times out. If the wrong Traffic Model ID is specified, the correct one will be returned by the interface. A value of -1 will always invoke the most recent traffic model

parameters.name: language
parameters.description: ISO 639-1 code for the output language. Supported languages are ar, ca, cs, da, de, el, en, en-GB, en-US, es, et, fi, fr, he, hu, id, in*, it, lt, lv, nb, nl, no, pl, pt, ro, ru, sk, sv, th, tr, zh

parameters.name: projection
parameters.description: The projection used to specify the coordinates in the request and response.  EPSG900913 (default) or EPSG4326

parameters.name: geometries
parameters.description: The type of vector geometry added to incidents (returned in the <v> element of the response).  Valid values are original which places incidents precisely on the road, or shifted which moves the incident slightly (depending on zoom level) to indicate specific road lanes

parameters.name: expandCluster
parameters.description: true or false to indicate whether to list all traffic incidents in a cluster separately

parameters.name: originalPosition
parameters.description:
true or false on whether to return the original position of the incident () as well as the one shifted to the beginning of the traffic tube (
